cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper addresses the problem of novelty detection in multiclass scenarios using machine learning techniques, which falls under the broad category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method is evaluated on image datasets, which suggests that it may also fall under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of an ensemble of classifiers and comparison of confidence values suggests that it may also fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the use of partitioning of training data suggests that it may also fall under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
